verdict: Speaker A (Destiny) won by maintaining relentless pressure on the specifics of Speaker B's (Econoboy) proposed system. While B attempted to lay out a complex theoretical framework, A consistently exposed its ambiguities and practical difficulties, particularly regarding capital allocation and the creation of new enterprises. A's strategy of acting as a persistent, practical skeptic proved more effective than B's abstract model-building. This forced B onto the defensive for much of the debate, allowing A to control the flow and framing of the core arguments.
